President Biden and Prime Minister Kishida of Japan spoke to reaffirm their commitment to Japan's defense after North Korea's recent ballistic missile launch. They strongly condemned the missile test and recognized it as a danger to Japan and the region, as well as a violation of UN resolutions. The leaders agreed to closely coordinate their response with South Korea and the international community. They also discussed the need to resolve the cases of Japanese citizens abducted by North Korea and limit its ability to support its missile and weapons programs.